6. A wireless communication reporter for wearing on a head of a user and detecting a radio signal of a radio transmitter comprising: 
a head mount; 
a radio frequency detector circuit having an indicator output, said radio frequency detector circuit (RFDC) supported by said head mount; 
an indicator coupled to the indicator output, wherein said indicator provides stimulus upon the radio frequency detector circuit receiving the radio signal.

17. A wireless communication reporter for wearing on a head comprising: 
a head mount; 
a radio frequency detector circuit having an indicator output, said radio frequency detector circuit mounted on said head mount; 
a light emitter, coupled to the indicator output and operative based on said indicator output, said light emitter having an anisotropic output directed along a principal ray, wherein said ray points in a direction of the user.
